Gunmen again on Friday night invaded a community in Nasarawa State, killing a police orderly and abducting the Chairman of Keffi Local Government Area, Muhammad Baba-Shehu. According to a report by the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN), the report was confirmed by the Police Public Relations Officer (PPRO) in the state,  ASP Ramhan Nansel. The PPRO said that based on preliminary investigation, the incident happened around 7:30 p.m. on Friday at Gudi Area of Akwanga Local Government Area.   9,204 sit for teachers’ qualifying exam     Kumuyi’s crusade: Confusion as Southeast youths, IPOB…     Trending video of ‘NDLEA officers in minibus’ is…   He added that one person, who was believed to be an aide to the chairman, was also abducted during the attack. According to the police spokesperson, Commissioner of Police, Adesina Soyemi, immediately deployed police personnel of the Anti-Kidnapping Unit and Police Mobile Force to the scene. He assured that the police would conduct a comprehensive investigation to unveil those responsible for the abduction and killing of the officer, rescue the victims and arrest the perpetrators. The PPRO, therefore, called on members of the public with useful information to contact any nearby police station.a